ay-School Hymnal'', American Lutheran Publication Board (March 9, 1901)<ref>[http://www.archive.org/details/sundayschoolhyml00unknuoft archive.org scan of the Sunday-School Hymnal] and [https://books.google.com/books?id=ClVCAAAAYAAJ Google Books Scan]</ref>\n**''Worship Supplement'', Concordia Publishing House (1969)<ref>{{cite book|title=Worship Supplement|url=https://archive.org/details/worshipsupplemen00luth|url-access=registration|year=1969|publisher=Concordia Publishing House|location=Saint Louis, MO|id=Unknown ID 75-92868<!--Looks like a LCCN, but did not match any records. -->}}</ref>\n*[[Lutheran Congregations in Mission for Christ]]\n**''[[ReClaim Hymnal]]'', Sola Publishing (2006)\n*[[North American Lutheran Church]]\n**''[[ReClaim Hymnal]]'', Sola Publishing (2006)\n*[[Protes'tant Conference]]\n**''A New Song'', John Springer\n*[[United Lutheran Church in America]]\n**''[[Common Service Book|Common Service Book with Hymnal]]'' (1918)\n*[[Wisconsin Evangelical Lutheran Synod]]\n**''[[Christian Worship: Supplement]]'' (2008)<ref>{{cite book|title=Christian Worship: Supplement|year=2008|publisher=Northwestern Publishing House|location=Milwaukee, WI|url=http://online.nph.net/p-407-christian-worship-supplement.aspx}}</ref>\n**''[[Christian Worship Hymnal|Christian Worship: A Lutheran Hymnal]]'' (1993)<ref>{{cite book|title=Christian Worship|year=1993|publisher=Northwestern Publishing House|location=Milwaukee, WI|isbn=978-0-8100-0422-1|url=http://online.nph.net/p-372-christian-worship-a-lutheran-hymnal-pew-edition.aspx}}</ref>\n{{col-end}}\n\n===[[Mennonite]]===\n*Philharmonia (1875) Reprinted and now updated by Old Order Mennonite Conference of Ontario.\n*Hymns and tunes for public and private worship, and Sunday schools compiled by a committee (1890)\n*Church and Sunday school hymnal, a collection of hymns and sacred songs, appropriate for church services, Sunday schools, and general devotional exercises. Compiled and published under the direction of a commit