ones story's title and plot details |publisher=Express |access-date=February 1, 2017 |date=February 1, 2017 |author=Simpson, George}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Fire & Blood (book)|Fire & Blood]]'' ||  2018 || Reference book & novella collection || The history of [[House Targaryen]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Winds of Winter]]'' || rowspan=2| TBD || rowspan=2| Novel || rowspan=2| ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]''\n|-\n| ''[[A Dream of Spring]]''\n|}\n\n===Editor===\n* ''New Voices in Science Fiction'' (1977: new stories by the [[John W. Campbell Award for Best New Writer|John W. Campbell Award]] winners)\n* ''New Voices in Science Fiction 2'' (1979: more new stories by the [[John W. Campbell Award for Best New Writer|John W. Campbell Award]] winners)\n* ''New Voices in Science Fiction 3'' (1980: more new stories by the [[John W. Campbell Award for Best New Writer|John W. Campbell Award]] winners)\n* ''New Voices in Science Fiction 4'' (1981: more new stories by the [[John W. Campbell Award for Best New Writer|John W. Campbell Award]] winners)\n* ''The Science Fiction Weight Loss Book'' (1983) edited with [[Isaac Asimov]] and [[Martin H. Greenberg]] (\"Stories by the Great Science Fiction Writers on Fat, Thin, and Everything in Between\")\n* ''The John W. Campbell Awards, Volume 5'' (1984, continuation of the ''New Voices in Science Fiction'' series)\n* ''Night Visions 3'' (1986)\n\n====''[[Wild Cards]]'' series editor (also contributor to many volumes)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wildcardsworld.com/the-books/|title=The Books {{!}} Wild Cards World|website=www.wildcardsworld.com|access-date=September 11, 2018}}</ref>====\n* ''[[Wild Cards (anthology)|Wild Cards]]'' (1987; contents expanded in 2010 edition with three new stories/authors)\n* ''[[Aces High (book)|Wild Cards II: Aces High]]'' (1987)\n* ''[[Jokers Wild (novel)|Wild Cards III: Jokers Wild]]'' (1987)\n* ''[[Aces Abroad|Wild Cards IV: Aces Abroad]]'' (1988; Book I of the Puppetman Quartet; contents expanded in 2015 edition with two new stories/authors)\n* ''[[Down and Dirty (book)|Wild Cards V: Down & Dirty]]'' (1988; Book II of the Puppetman Quartet)\n* ''Wild Cards VI: Ace in the Hole'' (1990; Book III of the Puppetman Quartet)\n* ''Wild Cards VII: Dead Man's Hand'' (1990; Book IV of the Puppetman Quartet)\n* ''Wild Cards VIII: One-Eyed Jacks'' (1991; Book I of the Rox Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards IX: Jokertown Shuffle'' (1991; Book II of the Rox Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards X: Double Solitaire'' (1992)\n* ''Wild Cards XI: Dealer's Choice'' (1992; Book III of the Rox Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XII: Turn of the Cards'' (1993)\n* ''[[Card Sharks (anthology)|Wild Cards XIII: Card Sharks]]'' (1993; Book I of the Card Shark Triad)\n* ''[[Marked Cards|Wild Cards XIV: Marked Cards]]'' (1994; Book II of the Card Shark Triad)\n* ''[[Black Trump|Wild Cards XV: Black Trump]]'' (1995; Book III of the Card Shark Triad)\n* ''[[Deuces Down|Wild Cards XVI: Deuces Down]]'' (2002)\n* ''Wild Cards XVII: Death Draws Five'' (2006; solo novel by [[John J. Miller (author)|John J. Miller]])\n* ''Wild Cards XVIII: Inside Straight'' (2008; Book I of ''The Committee'' triad)\n* ''Wild Cards IXX: Busted Flush'' (2008; Book II of ''The Committee'' triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XX: Suicide Kings'' (2009; Book III of ''The Committee'' triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXI: Fort Freak'' (2011; Book I of the Mean Streets Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXII: Lowball'' (2014; Book II of the Mean Streets Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXIII: High Stakes'' (2016; Book III of the Mean Streets Triad)<ref name=\"HighStakes\" />\n* ''Wild Cards XXIV: Mississippi Roll'' (2017; Book I of The American Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXV: Low Chicago'' (2018; Book II of The American Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXVI: Texas Hold 'Em'' (2018; Book III of The American Triad)\n* ''Wild Cards XXVII: Knaves Over Queens'' (2019)\n\n====Cross-genre anthologies edited (with [[Gardner Dozois]])====\n* ''[[Songs of the Dying Earth]]'' (2009; a tribute anthology to [[Jack Vance]]'s ''[[Dying Earth]]'' series, first published by [[Subterranean Press]])\n* ''[[Warriors (anthology)|Warriors]]'' (2010; a cross-genre anthology featuring stories about war and warriors; winner of the 2011 Locus Poll Award for Best Original Anthology)\n* ''[[Songs of Love and Death (anthology)|Songs of Love and Death]]'' (2010; a cross-genre anthology featuring stories of romance in fantasy and science fiction settings, originally entitled ''Star Crossed Lovers'')\n* ''[[Down These Strange Streets]]'' (2011; a cross-genre anthology that blends classic detective stories with fantasy and science fiction)\n* ''[[Old Mars]]'' (2013; a science fiction anthology featuring all new, retro-themed stories about the [[Mars|Red Planet]])<ref name=\"grrm.livejournal.com\" />\n* ''[[Dangerous Women (anthology)|Dangerous Women]]'' (2013;<ref name=\"Tor July 2013\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tor.com/blogs/2013/07/dangerous-women-tor-excerpts |title=''Dangerous Women'' Arrives on Tor.com |date=July 24, 2013 |access-date=November 19, 2013 |website=Tor.com}}</ref> a cross-genre anthology focusing on women warriors and strong female characters, originally titled ''Femmes Fatale'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grrm.livejournal.com/225206.html |title=Stuff and Nonsense |first=George R.R. |last=Martin |work=Not A Blog |date=July 2, 2011 |access-date=July 8, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215232922/http://grrm.livejournal.com/225206.html |archivedate=February 15, 2015 }}</ref>\n* ''[[Rogues (anthology)|Rogues]]'' (2014; a cross-genre anthology featuring new stories about assorted rogues)<ref name=\"grrm.livejournal.com\">{{cite web|url=http://grrm.livejournal.com/279376.html |title=Odds and Ends |first=George R.R. |last=Martin |work=Not A Blog |date=May 12, 2012 |access-date=July 8, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714220224/http://grrm.livejournal.com/279376.html |archivedate=July 14, 2014 }}</ref>\n* ''[[Old Venus]]'' (2015 publication; an anthology of all new, retro-themed [[Venus]] science fiction stories)<ref name=\"grrm.livejournal.com\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://grrm.livejournal.com/374059.html |title=Venus In March |first=George R.R. |last=Martin |work=Not A Blog |date=June 16, 2014 |access-date=July 8, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140620195301/http://grrm.livejournal.com/374059.html |archivedate=June 20, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n* ''[[The Hitchhiker (TV series)|The Hitchhiker]] ''\n** \"Remembering Melody\" (1984) \u2013 based on his short story\n* ''[[The Twilight Zone (1985 TV series)|The Twilight Zone]]''\n** \"[[The Last Defender of Camelot (The Twilight Zone)|The Last Defender of Camelot]]\" (1986) \u2013 writer (teleplay)\n** \"[[The Once and Future King (The Twilight Zone)|The Once and Future King]]\" (1986) \u2013 writer (teleplay), story editor\n** \"[[A Saucer of Loneliness (The Twilight Zone)|A Saucer of Loneliness]]\" (1986) \u2013 story editor\n** \"[[Lost and Found (The Twilight Zone)|Lost and Found]]\" (1986) \u2013 writer (teleplay), from a published short story by [[Phyllis Eisenstein]]\n** \"[[The World Next Door]]\" (1986) \u2013 story editor\n** \"[[The Toys of Caliban]]\" (1986) \u2013 writer (teleplay), from an unpublished short story by Terry Matz\n** \"[[The Road Less Traveled (The Twilight Zone)|The Road Less Traveled]]\" (1986) \u2013 writer (story and teleplay), story editor\n** \"[[The Girl I Married]]\" (1987) \u2013 story editor\n* ''[[Beauty and the Beast (1987 TV series)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' \u2013 co-supervising producer and executive story consultant\n** \"Terrible Saviour\" (1987) \u2013 writer\n** \"Masques\" (1987) \u2013 writer\n** \"Shades of Grey\" (1988) \u2013 writer\n** \"Promises of Someday\" (1988) \u2013 writer\n** \"Fever\" (1988) \u2013 writer\n** \"Ozymandias\" (1988) \u2013 writer\n** \"Dead of Winter\" (1988) \u2013 writer\n** \"Brothers\" (1989) \u2013 writer\n** \"When the Blue Bird Sings\" (1989) \u201